<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-12-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="194" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d194">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                        </head>
                        <p>In the course of his visit to Washington, March 14–18, 1953, Belgian
                            Foreign Minister <persName corresp="#p_VANZEELAND1">Van
                                Zeeland</persName> raised the issue of command structure and
                            jurisdiction within the central sector of <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>. For a record of his discussion of these topics, see
                            the memorandum of conversation by Assistant Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_MERCHANTLT1">Merchant</persName>, March 16, <ref target="#pg_773">page 773</ref>.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>